<subSubSection id="A8F166A64C77E358E4B0FA34FAB9F91C" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="582" pageId="4" pageNumber="581" type="description">
<paragraph id="E054352D4C77E359E4B0FA34FB43FA0F" blockId="4.[151,1437,1366,2041]" box="[199,1174,1438,1465]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C77E359E4B0FA34FE8CFA0E" bold="true" box="[199,345,1438,1464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="3F508B8F4C77E359E517FA35FE1DFA0F" box="[352,456,1439,1465]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Holotype</typeStatus>
female (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C77E359E65DFA35FDBAFA0F" box="[554,623,1439,1465]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1249,1273]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,181,1225]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[168,1419,181,1225]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sliochia adustifemur sp. nov., holotype, female, habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531158/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="271398C84C77E359E762FA34FCB8FA0F" box="[789,877,1438,1465]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="581" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
, fore wing length 
<quantity id="271398C84C77E359E04FFA35FB44FA0F" box="[1080,1169,1439,1465]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="581" unit="mm" value="3.4">3.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E054352D4C77E359E4B0FA69FE00F903" blockId="4.[151,1437,1366,2041]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C77E359E4B0FA69FEDBFA6B" bold="true" box="[199,270,1475,1501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Head.</emphasis>
Antenna with 25 flagellomeres; first flagellomere 1.2× longer than second flagellomere. Face (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C77E359E136FA69FA40FA6B" box="[1345,1429,1475,1501]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sliochia adustifemur sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesopleuron, lateral view C propodeum, dorsal view D first metasomal segment, lateral view E Hind first tarsal segment, lateral view F head, anterior view G head, dorsal view H mesoscutum, dorsal view I ovipositor J metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531160/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
) granulose. Clypeus (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C77E359E50CFA4DFE18F9B7" box="[379,461,1511,1537]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sliochia adustifemur sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesopleuron, lateral view C propodeum, dorsal view D first metasomal segment, lateral view E Hind first tarsal segment, lateral view F head, anterior view G head, dorsal view H mesoscutum, dorsal view I ovipositor J metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531160/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
) granulose, not convex in lateral view, apical margin slightly arched, sharp. Malar space granulose, its length 0.5× basal width of mandible. Mandible with a weak lamella, upper tooth slightly longer than lower tooth. Frons granulose, median carina absent. Vertex granulose. Inner margin of eye not indented opposite antennal socket. Interocellar distance (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C77E359E630F9F9FD75F9DB" box="[583,672,1619,1645]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sliochia adustifemur sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesopleuron, lateral view C propodeum, dorsal view D first metasomal segment, lateral view E Hind first tarsal segment, lateral view F head, anterior view G head, dorsal view H mesoscutum, dorsal view I ovipositor J metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531160/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
) 1.1× ocello-ocular distance and 1.5× distance between median and lateral ocelli. Temple granulose, mat, not swollen behind eyes. Occipital carina evenly arched, reaching hypostomal carina above mandible base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E054352D4C77E359E4B0F915FBE1F8DF" blockId="4.[151,1437,1366,2041]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C77E359E4B0F915FE99F96F" bold="true" box="[199,332,1727,1753]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Pronotum granulose-rugulose dorsally, mat, transversely striate below. Mesoscutum (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C77E359E14FF915FA41F96F" box="[1336,1428,1727,1753]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sliochia adustifemur sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesopleuron, lateral view C propodeum, dorsal view D first metasomal segment, lateral view E Hind first tarsal segment, lateral view F head, anterior view G head, dorsal view H mesoscutum, dorsal view I ovipositor J metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531160/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
) granulose, rugose on notaulic area. Scutellum and metanotum granulose. Mesopleuron (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C77E359E01BF949FB17F94B" box="[1132,1218,1763,1789]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sliochia adustifemur sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesopleuron, lateral view C propodeum, dorsal view D first metasomal segment, lateral view E Hind first tarsal segment, lateral view F head, anterior view G head, dorsal view H mesoscutum, dorsal view I ovipositor J metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531160/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) granulose, weakly transversely striate below tegula. Metapleuron granulose. Propodeum (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C77E359E7B7F8ADFBCCF897" box="[960,1049,1799,1825]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sliochia adustifemur sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesopleuron, lateral view C propodeum, dorsal view D first metasomal segment, lateral view E Hind first tarsal segment, lateral view F head, anterior view G head, dorsal view H mesoscutum, dorsal view I ovipositor J metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531160/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) with area basalis trapozoid; area superomedia confluent with area petiolaris, slightly depressed; area superomedia granulose-rugulose; area petiolaris rugose; area externa and area dentipara granulose; all carinae distinctly developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E054352D4C77E359E4B0F8D8FC82F84F" blockId="4.[151,1437,1366,2041]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C77E359E4B0F8D8FEDAF83A" bold="true" box="[199,271,1906,1932]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Wing.</emphasis>
Fore wing (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C77E359E5E2F8D9FE39F83B" box="[405,492,1907,1933]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sliochia adustifemur sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesopleuron, lateral view C propodeum, dorsal view D first metasomal segment, lateral view E Hind first tarsal segment, lateral view F head, anterior view G head, dorsal view H mesoscutum, dorsal view I ovipositor J metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531160/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
) areolet absent, length of vein M between 2rs-m and 2m-cu approx. 0.4× vein 2rs-m. Marginal cell short, distal part of surrounding vein 2.3× longer than proximal one. Vein 1cu-a opposite vein M&amp;RS, vein 1cu-a strongly oblique and angle with vein AA (60°). External angles of second discal cell nearly straight (80°). Hind wing with vein CU&amp;cu-a nearly vertical, not intercepted.
</paragraph>
<caption id="B49465A54C76E358E4E0FB4BFC82FB4F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531158" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6531158" box="[151,855,1249,1274]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531158/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="582" startId="5.[151,250,1249,1273]" targetBox="[168,1419,181,1225]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="E054352D4C76E358E4E0FB4BFC82FB4F" blockId="5.[151,855,1249,1274]" box="[151,855,1249,1274]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C76E358E4E0FB4BFEC6FB4F" bold="true" box="[151,275,1249,1273]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="27EB4EAE4C76E358E56EFB4BFE39FB4F" authority="Han &amp; Achterberg &amp; Chen, 2022" authorityName="Han &amp; Achterberg &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[281,492,1249,1273]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Sliochia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adustifemur" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C76E358E56EFB4BFE39FB4F" box="[281,492,1249,1273]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Sliochia adustifemur</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C76E358E585FB48FD96FB4C" bold="true" box="[498,579,1250,1274]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C9AC54444C76E358E585FB48FD96FB4C" box="[498,579,1250,1274]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype, female, habitus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E054352D4C76E358E4B0FA82FAC8FAD0" blockId="5.[151,1437,1320,1922]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C76E358E4B0FA82FED3FAF4" bold="true" box="[199,262,1320,1346]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Legs.</emphasis>
Hind femur 3.8× longer than wide. Inner spur of hind tibia 0.7× as long as first tarsomere of hind tarsus. First tarsal segment with ventral row of setae medially (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C76E358E77FFAE6FCB5FAD0" box="[776,864,1356,1382]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sliochia adustifemur sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesopleuron, lateral view C propodeum, dorsal view D first metasomal segment, lateral view E Hind first tarsal segment, lateral view F head, anterior view G head, dorsal view H mesoscutum, dorsal view I ovipositor J metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531160/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
). Tarsal claws weakly pectinate basally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E054352D4C76E358E4B0FADAFD95F988" blockId="5.[151,1437,1320,1922]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C76E358E4B0FADAFE9EFA3C" bold="true" box="[199,331,1392,1418]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Metasoma.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C76E358E517FADAFE66FA3C" box="[352,435,1392,1418]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sliochia adustifemur sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesopleuron, lateral view C propodeum, dorsal view D first metasomal segment, lateral view E Hind first tarsal segment, lateral view F head, anterior view G head, dorsal view H mesoscutum, dorsal view I ovipositor J metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531160/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Fig. 4J</figureCitation>
) First metasomal segment (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C76E358E776FADAFC8BFA3C" box="[769,862,1392,1418]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sliochia adustifemur sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesopleuron, lateral view C propodeum, dorsal view D first metasomal segment, lateral view E Hind first tarsal segment, lateral view F head, anterior view G head, dorsal view H mesoscutum, dorsal view I ovipositor J metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531160/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
) without glymma. First tergite 2.6× longer than width of postpetiole. Postpetiole granulose. Second tergite granulose-rugulose basally, smooth and shiny apically, 0.6× as long as first tergite, 0.8× longer than its apical width; thyridium transverse oval, its distance from basal margin of tergite 0.5× its length. Third tergite 0.8× longer than its apical width. Sixth and seventh tergites without medial emargination. From third tergite on smooth and shiny. Ovipositor (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C76E358E7ACF9AAFBFCF9AC" box="[987,1065,1536,1562]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[243,1345,181,1881]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sliochia adustifemur sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesopleuron, lateral view C propodeum, dorsal view D first metasomal segment, lateral view E Hind first tarsal segment, lateral view F head, anterior view G head, dorsal view H mesoscutum, dorsal view I ovipositor J metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531160/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Fig. 4I</figureCitation>
) straight, with a nodus before an inconspicuous dorsal subapical notch.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E054352D4C76E358E4B0F9EDFAB9F91C" blockId="5.[151,1437,1320,1922]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C76E358E4B0F9EDFEF5F9D7" bold="true" box="[199,288,1607,1633]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Colour.</emphasis>
Black. Mandible except teeth, scape and pedicel, palpi, tegula, fore and mid legs, hind coxa, trochanter, trochantellus and tibia basal 0.5, yellowish brown; hind femur and tibia apical 0.5, brown; hind tarsal segments blackish brown; metasoma from third segment on laterally yellowish brown, remainder of metasoma blackish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A8F166A64C76E358E4B0F919FDF9F979" box="[199,556,1715,1743]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E054352D4C76E358E4B0F919FDF9F979" blockId="5.[151,1437,1320,1922]" box="[199,556,1715,1743]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C76E358E4B0F919FEB4F97B" bold="true" box="[199,353,1715,1741]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="98FC75BD4C76E358E510F91EFE7FF978" box="[359,426,1716,1742]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="222FFBCF4C76E358E5CEF91EFDF5F979" box="[441,544,1716,1743]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A8F166A64C76E358E4B0F972FEC4F88C" pageId="5" pageNumber="582" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E054352D4C76E358E4B0F972FEC4F88C" blockId="5.[151,1437,1320,1922]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C76E358E4B0F972FEC4F944" bold="true" box="[199,273,1752,1778]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Notes.</emphasis>
We have placed this new species in 
<taxonomicName id="27EB4EAE4C76E358E6CCF972FCC2F944" authorityName="Gauld" authorityYear="1976" box="[699,791,1752,1778]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Sliochia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C76E358E6CCF972FCC2F944" box="[699,791,1752,1778]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Sliochia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because the new species matches the generic characters well. The new species differs distinctly from the only other known species of this genus, 
<taxonomicName id="27EB4EAE4C76E358E0E5F956FB37F8A0" authorityName="Gauld" authorityYear="1976" box="[1170,1250,1788,1814]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Sliochia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bala">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C76E358E0E5F956FB37F8A0" box="[1170,1250,1788,1814]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">S. bala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as shown in the key above.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A8F166A64C76E358E4B0F8EEFEE5F834" pageId="5" pageNumber="582" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E054352D4C76E358E4B0F8EEFEE5F834" blockId="5.[151,1437,1320,1922]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C76E358E4B0F8EEFE9BF8E8" bold="true" box="[199,334,1860,1886]" pageId="5" pageNumber="582">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name derived from “adustus” (Latin for “brown”) and “femur” (Latin for “thigh”), because its hind femur brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
